SECTION 3 — PER-VERSION GRANT AND REVOCATION
--------------------------------------------
The grant applies on a per-version basis:

(a) Versions obtained while starred — For any version of the Software you
    obtained, copied, built, or ran while your star was active, the grant
    in Section 2 is irrevocable for that version, even if you later unstar
    the repository. The star is a one-time key for the versions you held
    while it was active, not a subscription for them.

(b) Future versions after unstarring — If you unstar the repository, NO
    grant is offered for any version released, published, or obtained after
    you unstarred. To use a later version, you must star the repository
    again at the time you obtain it. Continued use of versions released
    after you unstarred, without re-starring, is unauthorized ("piracy").


